Here's the consolidated design system used across all the sections we've built:
Color Scheme — "Premium Red & Purple"
Background

Base background: bg-[#0a0710] (near-black with slight purple undertone)
Card backgrounds: bg-white/[0.02] to bg-white/[0.05] (subtle translucent overlays)
Card borders: border-white/10

Accent gradient (primary brand gradient)

Used for: headline highlight text, buttons, icons, numbers
from-red-500 via-fuchsia-500 to-purple-500 (text/gradient text)
from-red-500 to-purple-600 (buttons/solid gradients)

Badge/pill style

Border: border-red-500/30
Background: bg-gradient-to-r from-red-950/60 to-purple-950/60
Dot: bg-red-500 with animate-pulse
Text: gradient from-red-400 to-purple-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent

Glow accents (background blobs)

bg-red-600/10, bg-purple-700/10, bg-fuchsia-600/10 — all blur-3xl rounded-full

Text colors

Headings: text-white
Body/subtext: text-gray-400 (hover state often text-gray-300)
Muted/labels: text-gray-500

Hover states

Border glow: hover:border-red-500/40
Shadow glow: hover:shadow-[0_10px_40px_rgba(225,29,72,0.2)] (varies 0.15–0.25 opacity)
Text shift: solid white → gradient from-red-400 to-purple-400 bg-clip-text

